Spanish police on Wednesday arrested Herve Falciani, who was convicted in Switzerland of industrial espionage after leaking clients’ tax information. ZURICH - Switzerland’s justice ministry on Thursday submitted a formal request for the extradition of Swiss bank whistleblower Herve Falciani from Spain. “The Federal Office of Justice on 5 April transmitted a formal request for extradition via diplomatic channels,” a spokesman said in an emailed statement. Spanish police on Wednesday arrested Falciani, a former employee of HSBC’s Swiss private bank, who was convicted in Switzerland of industrial espionage after leaking clients’ tax information.